# <type>: <subject> (max 50 chars)
# |<----  Using a Maximum Of 50 Characters  ---->|


# <body> (wrap at 72 chars)
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|


# 📋 Documentation Checklist
# ---------------------------
# Did you update relevant docs?
# - [ ] docs/ROADMAP.md (if feature complete/changed)
# - [ ] docs/CHANGELOG.md (always update for features/fixes)
# - [ ] docs/TECHNICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md (if architecture changed)
# - [ ] docs/README.md (if status changed)


# 🏷️  Type (choose one):
# ----------------------
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# style:    Formatting, missing semi colons, etc (no code change)
# refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf:     Performance improvement
# test:     Adding missing tests
# chore:    Build process, tooling, dependencies


# 💡 Writing Good Commit Messages:
# --------------------------------
# Subject line:
#   - Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
#   - Don't end with period
#   - Capitalize first letter
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why (not how)
#   - Reference docs: "See docs/ROADMAP.md Phase 1A"
#   - Reference issues: "Fixes #123"
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#
# Examples:
#   feat: Add multi-trip dashboard with card grid
#   fix: Prevent localStorage quota exceeded error
#   docs: Update ROADMAP.md Phase 1A progress
#   refactor: Extract trip manager to separate module


# 📚 Documentation References:
# ----------------------------
# - ROADMAP.md: docs/ROADMAP.md
# - ARCHITECTURE: docs/TECHNICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md
# - WORKFLOW: docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md
